47 btCollisionShape* createShapePrimitive(const shapes::Box* geom, const CollisionObjectType& collision_object_type)
48 {
49  assert(collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::USE_SHAPE_TYPE);
50  const double* size = geom->size;
51  btScalar a = static_cast<btScalar>(size[0] / 2);
52  btScalar b = static_cast<btScalar>(size[1] / 2);
53  btScalar c = static_cast<btScalar>(size[2] / 2);
54 
55  return (new btBoxShape(btVector3(a, b, c)));
56 }

80 btCollisionShape* createShapePrimitive(const shapes::Mesh* geom, const CollisionObjectType& collision_object_type,
81  CollisionObjectWrapper* cow)
82 {
83  assert(collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::USE_SHAPE_TYPE ||
84  collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::CONVEX_HULL ||
85  collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::SDF);
86 
87  if (geom->vertex_count > 0 && geom->triangle_count > 0)
88  {
89  // convert the mesh to the assigned collision object type
90  switch (collision_object_type)
91  {
92  case CollisionObjectType::CONVEX_HULL:
93  {
94  // Create a convex hull shape to approximate Trimesh
95  collision_detection_bullet::AlignedVector<Eigen::Vector3d> input;
96  collision_detection_bullet::AlignedVector<Eigen::Vector3d> vertices;
97  std::vector<int> faces;
98 
99  input.reserve(geom->vertex_count);
100  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < geom->vertex_count; ++i)
101  input.push_back(Eigen::Vector3d(geom->vertices[3 * i], geom->vertices[3 * i + 1], geom->vertices[3 * i + 2]));
102 
103  if (collision_detection_bullet::createConvexHull(vertices, faces, input) < 0)
104  return nullptr;
105 
106  btConvexHullShape* subshape = new btConvexHullShape();
107  for (const Eigen::Vector3d& v : vertices)
108  subshape->addPoint(
109  btVector3(static_cast<btScalar>(v[0]), static_cast<btScalar>(v[1]), static_cast<btScalar>(v[2])));
110 
111  return subshape;
112  }
113  case CollisionObjectType::USE_SHAPE_TYPE:
114  {
115  btCompoundShape* compound =
116  new btCompoundShape(BULLET_COMPOUND_USE_DYNAMIC_AABB, static_cast<int>(geom->triangle_count));
117  compound->setMargin(
118  BULLET_MARGIN); // margin: compound seems to have no effect when positive but has an effect when negative
119 
120  for (unsigned i = 0; i < geom->triangle_count; ++i)
121  {
122  btVector3 v[3];
123  for (unsigned x = 0; x < 3; ++x)
124  {
125  unsigned idx = geom->triangles[3 * i + x];
126  for (unsigned y = 0; y < 3; ++y)
127  {
128  v[x][y] = static_cast<btScalar>(geom->vertices[3 * idx + y]);
129  }
130  }
131 
132  btCollisionShape* subshape = new btTriangleShapeEx(v[0], v[1], v[2]);
133  if (subshape != nullptr)
134  {
135  cow->manage(subshape);
136  subshape->setMargin(BULLET_MARGIN);
137  btTransform geom_trans;
138  geom_trans.setIdentity();
139  compound->addChildShape(geom_trans, subshape);
140  }
141  }
142 
143  return compound;
144  }
145  default:
146  {
147  ROS_ERROR("This bullet shape type (%d) is not supported for geometry meshs",
148  static_cast<int>(collision_object_type));
149  return nullptr;
150  }
151  }
152  }
153  ROS_ERROR("The mesh is empty!");
154  return nullptr;
155 }

157 btCollisionShape* createShapePrimitive(const shapes::OcTree* geom, const CollisionObjectType& collision_object_type,
158  CollisionObjectWrapper* cow)
159 {
160  assert(collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::USE_SHAPE_TYPE ||
161  collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::CONVEX_HULL ||
162  collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::SDF ||
163  collision_object_type == CollisionObjectType::MULTI_SPHERE);
164 
165  btCompoundShape* subshape =
166  new btCompoundShape(BULLET_COMPOUND_USE_DYNAMIC_AABB, static_cast<int>(geom->octree->size()));
167  double occupancy_threshold = geom->octree->getOccupancyThres();
168 
169  // convert the mesh to the assigned collision object type
170  switch (collision_object_type)
171  {
172  case CollisionObjectType::USE_SHAPE_TYPE:
173  {
174  for (auto it = geom->octree->begin(static_cast<unsigned char>(geom->octree->getTreeDepth())),
175  end = geom->octree->end();
176  it != end; ++it)
177  {
178  if (it->getOccupancy() >= occupancy_threshold)
179  {
180  double size = it.getSize();
181  btTransform geom_trans;
182  geom_trans.setIdentity();
183  geom_trans.setOrigin(btVector3(static_cast<btScalar>(it.getX()), static_cast<btScalar>(it.getY()),
184  static_cast<btScalar>(it.getZ())));
185  btScalar l = static_cast<btScalar>(size / 2);
186  btBoxShape* childshape = new btBoxShape(btVector3(l, l, l));
187  childshape->setMargin(BULLET_MARGIN);
188  cow->manage(childshape);
189 
190  subshape->addChildShape(geom_trans, childshape);
191  }
192  }
193  return subshape;
194  }
195  case CollisionObjectType::MULTI_SPHERE:
196  {
197  for (auto it = geom->octree->begin(static_cast<unsigned char>(geom->octree->getTreeDepth())),
198  end = geom->octree->end();
199  it != end; ++it)
200  {
201  if (it->getOccupancy() >= occupancy_threshold)
202  {
203  double size = it.getSize();
204  btTransform geom_trans;
205  geom_trans.setIdentity();
206  geom_trans.setOrigin(btVector3(static_cast<btScalar>(it.getX()), static_cast<btScalar>(it.getY()),
207  static_cast<btScalar>(it.getZ())));
208  btSphereShape* childshape =
209  new btSphereShape(static_cast<btScalar>(std::sqrt(2 * ((size / 2) * (size / 2)))));
210  childshape->setMargin(BULLET_MARGIN);
211  cow->manage(childshape);
212 
213  subshape->addChildShape(geom_trans, childshape);
214  }
215  }
216  return subshape;
217  }
218  default:
219  {
220  ROS_ERROR("This bullet shape type (%d) is not supported for geometry octree",
221  static_cast<int>(collision_object_type));
222  return nullptr;
223  }
224  }
225 }

227 btCollisionShape* createShapePrimitive(const shapes::ShapeConstPtr& geom,
228  const CollisionObjectType& collision_object_type, CollisionObjectWrapper* cow)
229 {
230  switch (geom->type)
231  {
232  case shapes::BOX:
233  {
234  return createShapePrimitive(static_cast<const shapes::Box*>(geom.get()), collision_object_type);
235  }
236  case shapes::SPHERE:
237  {
238  return createShapePrimitive(static_cast<const shapes::Sphere*>(geom.get()), collision_object_type);
239  }
240  case shapes::CYLINDER:
241  {
242  return createShapePrimitive(static_cast<const shapes::Cylinder*>(geom.get()), collision_object_type);
243  }
244  case shapes::CONE:
245  {
246  return createShapePrimitive(static_cast<const shapes::Cone*>(geom.get()), collision_object_type);
247  }
248  case shapes::MESH:
249  {
250  return createShapePrimitive(static_cast<const shapes::Mesh*>(geom.get()), collision_object_type, cow);
251  }
252  case shapes::OCTREE:
253  {
254  return createShapePrimitive(static_cast<const shapes::OcTree*>(geom.get()), collision_object_type, cow);
255  }
256  default:
257  {
258  ROS_ERROR("This geometric shape type (%d) is not supported using BULLET yet", static_cast<int>(geom->type));
259  return nullptr;
260  }
261  }

264 CollisionObjectWrapper::CollisionObjectWrapper(const std::string& name, const collision_detection::BodyType& type_id,
265  const std::vector<shapes::ShapeConstPtr>& shapes,
266  const AlignedVector<Eigen::Isometry3d>& shape_poses,
267  const std::vector<CollisionObjectType>& collision_object_types,
268  bool active)
269  : m_name(name)
270  , m_type_id(type_id)
271  , m_shapes(shapes)
272  , m_shape_poses(shape_poses)
273  , m_collision_object_types(collision_object_types)
274 {
275  if (shapes.empty() || shape_poses.empty() ||
276  (shapes.size() != shape_poses.size() || collision_object_types.empty() ||
277  shapes.size() != collision_object_types.size()))
278  {
279  throw std::exception();
280  }
281 
282  this->setContactProcessingThreshold(BULLET_DEFAULT_CONTACT_DISTANCE);
283  assert(!name.empty());
284 
285  if (active)
286  {
287  m_collisionFilterGroup = btBroadphaseProxy::KinematicFilter;
288  m_collisionFilterMask = btBroadphaseProxy::KinematicFilter | btBroadphaseProxy::StaticFilter;
289  }
290  else
291  {
292  m_collisionFilterGroup = btBroadphaseProxy::StaticFilter;
293  m_collisionFilterMask = btBroadphaseProxy::KinematicFilter;
294  }
295 
296  if (shapes.size() == 1)
297  {
298  btCollisionShape* shape = createShapePrimitive(m_shapes[0], collision_object_types[0], this);
299  shape->setMargin(BULLET_MARGIN);
300  manage(shape);
301  setCollisionShape(shape);
302  setWorldTransform(convertEigenToBt(m_shape_poses[0]));
303  }
304  else
305  {
306  btCompoundShape* compound =
307  new btCompoundShape(BULLET_COMPOUND_USE_DYNAMIC_AABB, static_cast<int>(m_shapes.size()));
308  manage(compound);
309  // margin on compound seems to have no effect when positive but has an effect when negative
310  compound->setMargin(BULLET_MARGIN);
311  setCollisionShape(compound);
312 
313  setWorldTransform(convertEigenToBt(m_shape_poses[0]));
314  Eigen::Isometry3d inv_world = m_shape_poses[0].inverse();
315 
316  for (std::size_t j = 0; j < m_shapes.size(); ++j)
317  {
318  btCollisionShape* subshape = createShapePrimitive(m_shapes[j], collision_object_types[j], this);
319  if (subshape != nullptr)
320  {
321  manage(subshape);
322  subshape->setMargin(BULLET_MARGIN);
323  btTransform geom_trans = convertEigenToBt(inv_world * m_shape_poses[j]);
324  compound->addChildShape(geom_trans, subshape);
325  }
326  }
327  }
328 }
